flagicon|China}} Chinese Champion 2014, 2015 & 2016.<ref name=\"art\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of beatboxers]]\n*[[Grand Beatbox Battle]]\n*[[UK Beatbox Championships]]\n*[[Breath Control: The History of the Human Beat Box]]\n*[[Mouth drumming]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n<!--======================== {{No more links}} ============================\n    | PLEASE BE CAUTIOUS IN ADDING MORE LINKS TO THIS ARTICLE. Wikipedia  |\n    | is not a collection of links nor should it be used for advertising. |\n    |                                                                     |\n    |           Excessive or inappropriate links WILL BE DELETED.         |\n    | See [[Wikipedia:External links]] & [[Wikipedia:Spam]] for details.  |\n    |                                                                     |\n    | If there are already plentiful links, please propose additions or   |\n    | replacements on this article's discussion page, or submit your link |\n    | to the relevant category at the Open Directory Project (dmoz.org)   |\n    | and link back to that category using the {{dmoz}} template.         |\n==={{No more links}}=========-->\n\n* [http://swissbeatbox.com Swissbeatbox.com] - World's largest Beatbox Platform.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160423223935/http://beatboxbattle.tv/ Beatboxbattle.tv] - Organizer of the World Beatbox Championship.\n* [https://humanbeatbox.com Humanbeatbox.com] - One of the first Beatboxing Online-Communities.\n\n[[Category:Beatboxing]]\n[[Category:World championships]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 2005]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Beatbox Battle World Championship''' (BBBWC) is hosted triennially (every three years) hosted by Beatbox Battle Tv in a week-long festival held in [[Berlin]], Germany. Face-to-face beatbox battles take place in five different categories:- individual male, individual female, tag-team, crew battle and loop station. In 2015, more than 150 national or major event champions of [[beatboxing]] gathered from 50 or so countries, after qualifying to participate in the world event by winning their respective national championships.<ref name=\"human\" /><ref name=\"reddit\" />\n\n[[File:Festival des Vieilles Charrues 2015 - Krismenn & Alem - 030.jpg|thumb|right|Alem (World Champion 2015) en concert sur le Festival des Vieilles Charrues 2015]]\n[[File:Butterscotch at Montreux Jazz Festival.jpg|thumb|right|Butterscotch (World Champion 2005) at the Montreux Jazz Festival 2012]]\n\n==History==\nThe first ever Beatbox Battle World Championship was started in 2005 by Alexander \u201cBeeLow\u201d B\u00fclow<ref name=\"boots\">{{cite web|url=http://www.diva-portal.org/smash/get/diva2:851567/FULLTEXT01.pdf |title=Boots and cats!: Beatboxing from a pedagogical perspective |publisher=Sherman, P. Royal College of Music in Stockholm, Department of Music Education. |date=2015 |accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> and took place in 2005 in [[Leipzig]], Germany.  The event was the first international [[beatboxing]] championship.<ref name=\"human\" /><ref name=\"reddit\" />\n\nThe second Beatbox Battle World Championship, took place at the 2BE Club am Hauptbahnhof near Berlin-Central Station in 2009.<ref name=\"epho\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ephotozine.com/article/beatbox-battle-world-championship-2009-11630 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140723171202/http://www.ephotozine.com/article/beatbox-battle-world-championship-2009-11630 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2014-07-23 |title=Beatbox Battle World Championship 2009 /ephotozine.com |date=2009}}</ref>\n\nThe 3rd BBBWC in 2012, the 4th in 2015 and the 5th in 2018 were held at the Astra Kulturhaus in [[Friedrichshain-Kreuzberg]], Berlin.<ref name=\"astra\">{{cite web|url=https://www.astra-berlin.de/events/2015-05-29-beatbox-battle-world-championship |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103011711/https://www.astra-berlin.de/events/2015-05-29-beatbox-battle-world-championship |url-status=dead |archive-date=2018-01-03 |title=2015-05-29 Beatbox Battle World Championship /astra-berlin.de |date=2015 }}</ref>\n\nMore than 150 artists from 6 continents and 50 countries qualified for the event, including musicians from [[Argentina]], [[Australia]], [[Brazil]], [[Canada]], [[Chile]], [[China]], [[Colombia]], [[Ecuador]], [[Indonesia]], [[Japan]], [[Malaysia]], [[Mexico]], [[Morocco]], [[New Zealand]], [[Peru]], [[Philippines]],<ref name=\"phil\">{{cite web|url=http://www.philippine-embassy.de/bln/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=1349&Itemid=190 |title=Pinoy beatbox pride to compete at the Beatbox Battle World Championships |publisher= philippine-embassy.de |date=2015 |accessdate=January 2, 2018}}</ref> [[Singapore]], [[Venezuela]], [[Vietnam]], [[South Africa]], [[Russia]], [[South Korea]], [[Taiwan]], [[United States]],  + 26 European countries were invited to perform in front of around 1,500 spectators.<ref name=\"swiss2015\">{{cite web |url=http://www.swissbeatbox.com/beatbox-battle-world-championship-2015/ |title=Beatbox Battle World Championship 2015 |publisher=swissbeatbox.com |date=2015 |accessdate=January 2, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108132338/http://www.swissbeatbox.com/beatbox-battle-world-championship-2015/ |archive-date=January 8, 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n==Event format and qualification==\nAll competitors have had to qualify for the Beatbox Battle World Championship by winning their national Beatbox Battle championships, or having reached the knock-out stages of the previous Beatbox Battle World Championship, wildcard or special invitation.<ref name=\"face1\">{{cite web|url=https://beatboxbattle.com/championship/men-category/ |title=System of the contest |publisher= beatboxbattle.com |date=2018 |accessdate=March 10, 2018}}</ref>\nIn the first round, each performer has two minutes time to demonstrate their skills to an international panel of elite judges from the [[beatboxing]] world, (such as [[Reeps One]] of England)<ref name=\"swiss2015\" /> and previous world champions from this tournament, to decide which performers qualify for the Knock-out rounds that are contested in \u2018battle mode\u2019 to determine the world champion. The judges base their decision on musicality, technicality,originality, pattern  and show quality on the stage.<ref name=\"swiss2015\" />\n\n==Wildcards==\nTo qualify for the tournament, a beatboxer has to qualify by winning their national championships. however, there are exceptions to this rule.\nSome international events are also recognized by the World Championship committee. This was the case for Gene Shinozaki and Dharni, winners of the Grand Beatbox Battles, were invited to compete in the World Championships 2015. There was also a wildcard competition for 2018, where wannabe contenders entered a video for judgement to win a place at the 2018 BBBWC.<ref name=\"swiss2015\" /> The results of the 2018 Wildcard event were as follows:<ref name=\"wild\">{{cite web|url=https://beatboxbattle.com/wildcard-winner-2018/ |title=wildcard winners 2018 |publisher= beatboxbattle.com |date=2018 |accessdate=May 20, 2018}}</ref>\n\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=8&v=ofbE-oLtCWo Audical {{flagu|United States}} Mens Solo winner] \n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=2&v=TXv3_viLT2c Madox {{flagu|Germany}} Mens Solo 2nd Place] \n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1&v=VTw8I0f5iMs Cosmin {{flagu|Romania}} Mens Solo 3rd Place] \n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1&v=2I_Vd41Phfc So-So {{flagu|Japan}} Loopstation winner] \n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=1&v=be85CA2UBbM BreZ {{flagu|France}} Loopstation 2nd place]\n\n==BBBWC Results==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: left\"\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" align=\"left\" bgcolor=\"#1e90ff\" |<span style=\"color:black;\">'''Individual Male'''</span>\n|-\n!Edition\n!Year\n!Venue\n!Champion\n!Vice Champion\n!Video/Reference\n|-\n| 1st BBBWC\